Abdomen.
Brown with pattern of silvery-gray pruinosity (
Fig. 1
); syntergite 1+2, T3 and T4 each with one lateral marginal seta, T4 with one pair of stronger median marginal setae, T5 with about 18 marginal setae; ST5 with short lobes, apically expanded and truncated (
Figs 1–2
).
